   <h1>The Troll&#39;s Bane Chronicle</h1>

   <h2>The third year of the new era: August</h2>

<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 1st, Dyluck summons all citizens to touch base with himself, Crosis or Korwin, to contract in the army for the fight against Darlok. Many put their names on the hanging out listings.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 2nd, the first release of the Troll's Bane newspaper, published by Elvin Shaeron occurs, the following day, the second release is published.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 4th, the Clan of Axe publishes a listing of citizens, being banned out of Silverbrand. The listing will be elongated steady.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 5th, Athian intimates the foundation of the Order of the Seeker. It is an order, worshipping Cherga to help the goddess get back the glory she used to have.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 7th, Elaralith attacks Silverbrand and two dwarves just as the Irmorom antlered altar. Therefore, she is sent to jail.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 9th, one more time a release of the newspaper is being published. It will be the last release.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 9th, the ogre-cave is declared to be the tribes' cave of the Bloodskull Clan, trespassing will be punished with death.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 9th, the dwarves of Silverbrand and the Bloodskull Clan sign a peace treaty: Dwarves and orcs aren't allowed to enter the others rooms, attacks against each other are prohibited.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 9th, Grant Herion announces in the name of Darlok, that everyone, being grabbed in Darloks territory, will have to pay 200 gold pieces as punishment. Moreover it is prohibited by death penalty, to attack or even kill the ogre-guards.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 10th, the order of the Grey Light intimates the relocation of its public representation, just as the preferment of some of its members. At the same time Elaralith is expelled from the order, because of repeated disrespect to the codex.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 11th, the Lyrenzia Foundation publishes the conditions for guilds or groups to get registered.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 11th, Grant Herion invoices "The Movement" to fight against Elaralith and her friends.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 11th, Elaralith attacks the Bloodskull cave, citizens of the town and Silverbrand. The reason she gave was, that Silverbrand and the Bloodkulls would be evil and therefore would have to be fought.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 12th, Grant Herion founds The Movement, a foundation of fighters, fighting off one's own bat the things they declare to be evil. Because the founder is being known as a supporter of Darlok, the aims of this arrangement are more than dodgy.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 13th, the Grey Rose declares war to Darlok and his supporters, because of the desecration of a grave and an attack on a knight. Later it is exposed, that the attack wasn't gone out of Darlok, but out of one of Darloks land guarding Orc of the Bloodskull Clan named Pok'Ash.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 13th, Elvymir announces the reopening of Eldamar, under the leadership of himself. For being as good as unknown he is met with opposition from the other elves. For at least being improperly, the control of the Elven Community switches over to Moathia Nethiala.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 13th, Wiergraf and Pok'Ash beg off at the Grey Rose and want to speak with its leaders. The conversations of Aragon and Pok'Ash fail, because of his irrationality.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 13th, Gorr Tarak is looking for some brave fellow citizens, to sally and put an end to the drought. Different proposals are made, several books are quoted. Sunny Holz, Xaveria, Magor, Ultoris and Denon at least join the mission.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 14th, the councilmen election and the election of the SMACC council are deferred.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 14th, the Grey Rose makes a peace treaty to Darlok. Therefore Darlok shall conclude the drought. Darlok defeats.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 14th, the renovated castle of the Lyrenzia Foundation is made available for the public.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 15th and 17th, Tialdin invoices, that Salathe and Croktin Skullcrusher are members of the tavern crew from now on.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 16th, the return of L&uacute;thien Falassion and Alice is intimated.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 16th, the election of the public councilman of Lyrenzia starts. Fieps wins the election with 9 votes. Zerbus got 4 and Drogla 1 vote.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 16th, the election for the SMACC council starts. Elected is Moathia Nethiale with 5 votes and Fedaykin with 12 votes. Drogla got 2 votes.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 17th, the Grey Rose and the Bloodskull Clan negotiate the conditions of a peace treaty, which is never been ratified by Veralion, the leader of the orcs. The efforts fizzle.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 17th, the orc Kzarak Zhoruch reports, that all fishes seem to be dead.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 18th, Sean Elaski alias "The Returner" official invoices his homecoming. He, who had changed in the years he was gone, had come, to volunteer the citizens of Troll's Bane during the terrible drought.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 18th, a huge glowing rock came down from heaven and many wonder if this rock is a threat, whilst others don't believe in the report of the discoverer of this phenomenon.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 20th, Belegi and Draakon invite all people to the second dance contest. It takes place on August 31st, according to plan.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 20th, Sean Elaski complains at Veralion, for his orcs attacking himself and some others without any reason. He asks the leader of the Bloodskulls and his orcs to put the lid on this offence and Veralion promises to do so.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 22nd, Alnerith warns of monsters in town. Many report their experiences with monsters.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, in the course of the month August, many authors draw up scripts against Lyrenzia and allude on allegedly mistakes in the organisation, that they seem to have found personally. On the other hand there are some people exclaiming for war against Darlok. Both topics are discussed for a long time.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 26th, an unknown person pins up a note, asking if the citizens of Troll's Bane really want Darlok to be their ruler. A dispute between Grant Herion and the unknown writer flares.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 26th, Yataghan asks for the Troll's Bane as it was once upon a time. No one is able to give him a precise answer.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 26th, Salathe put up a tad deflagrated parchment and starts his journey.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 27th, once again a trial against Elaralith starts. A long discussion about her person flares. Elaralith is declared not guilty in this case.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 28th, Gnarr is looking for a lizard wife. Saurin Talon seems not to be uninterested in finding one, too.</p>
<p>In year 3 of the new age, on August 29th, Lyrenzia publishes a listing, showing, who has been imprisoned for how long, starting with trial #22.</p>

